    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing around 25 species of coarse grasses, many with with reddish to purplish-black panicles, growing to 2 m in height. These grasses are cultivated for food and forage worldwide, but some species have escaped cultivation and are troublesome agricultural weeds in temperate to tropical regions throughout the world. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
